					<img class="image-bg stellar" src="/var/esa/storage/images/applications/observing_the_earth/cryosat/19716620-12-eng-GB/CryoSat_pillars.jpg" alt="CryoSat" data-stellar-ratio="0.8"> 
</section>

<section class="mission-details">
	<div class="mission-intro">
		
		<a name="eztoc19726850_1" id="eztoc19726850_1"></a><h2><b>The mission</b></h2><p>ESA’s Earth Explorer CryoSat mission is dedicated to measuring the thickness of polar sea ice and monitoring changes in the ice sheets that blanket Greenland and Antarctica.&nbsp;Its main payload is a&nbsp;SAR Interferometric Radar Altimeter, which&nbsp;is designed for ice, measuring changes at the margins of vast ice sheets and floating ice in polar oceans.</p>
	</div>
	<div class="mission-data">
		
		<a name="eztoc19727873_1" id="eztoc19727873_1"></a><h2><b>The launch</b></h2>
<ul>

<li><b>Date: </b>08 April 2010</li>

<li><b>Site:&nbsp;</b>Baikonur Cosmodrome, Kazakhstan</li>

<li><b>Rocket:&nbsp;</b>Russian/Ukrainian Dnepr based on SS-18 intercontinental ballistic missile</li>

</ul>

	</div>
		<div class="mission-logo">
		<img src="/var/esa/storage/images/applications/observing_the_earth/cryosat/19728896-31-eng-GB/CryoSat_pillars.jpg"> 
	</div>
	</section>

<section class="mission-stats connecting-benefiting">
	
		
		
<ul>

<li><a href="http://www.esa.int/Applications/Observing_the_Earth/CryoSat/Instruments"><b>1st</b></a>&nbsp;altimeter of its kind</li>

<li><a href="http://www.esa.int/Applications/Observing_the_Earth/CryoSat/CryoSat_still_cool_at_10"><b>10+ yrs</b></a>&nbsp;in orbit</li>

<li><a href="http://www.esa.int/Applications/Observing_the_Earth/CryoSat/Facts_and_figures"><b>719 km</b></a>&nbsp;mean altitude</li>

<li><a href="http://www.esa.int/Applications/Observing_the_Earth/CryoSat/Facts_and_figures"><b>92°</b></a> inclination</li>

</ul>

	
